			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><b>By <a href="http://www.nickdichario.com/">Nick Dichario</a> and <a href="http://www.fortunecity.com/tattooine/farmer/2/">Mike Resnick</a>.</b><br />
Read by Stephen Eley.<br />
First appeared in <i>Science Fiction Age</i>, November 1994.<br /></p>

<p><i>So there you have him, Frederick Bannister, tripping across the highways and byways of of life, stubbing a toe here, bruising an elbow there, spilling this, dropping that, and managing to make it to the halfway point without too many major accomplishments or disasters.</i></p>

<p><i>And what of Wilma?</i></p>

